4:
Why do people even bother posting
requests like these? The reward is
awful!
5:
Super out of the way, too. That's
gonna be a pass from me!
8:
Grieg, what's up? Request catch
your eye?
16:
Oof, the reward on this one is
terrible. No wonder nobody's picked
this up yet.
20:
Everyone, I beg you. Please take on
this request!
24:
Oh, this must be the village you
were talking about before...
31:
Oh goodness, if it isn't Grieg! You've
come back!
35:
Haha! It's been a long time, Elder! I'm
glad to see everyone's doing well
too.
39:
But... we don't have time to
reminisce about the past. I'm here
because of the request you put out.
40:
Could you update us on the
situation so far?
45:
I see. The enemy is 30 men strong. I
worry if we can handle that, given
our numbers disadvantage.
48:
Grieg, what do you think we should
do?
51:
Don't worry, Elder! You can leave it to
ME!
55: That mean you cooked up a plan?
62:
But, I've got you guys, right?! I was
planning on relying on you!
66:
Seriously? This guy.
All right, let's mobilize this old folks'
home. Get movin', grandpas.
69:
We'll have you build a barricade.
Just something annoying enough to
buy us a few minutes of time.
73: We'll be doing the actual fighting.
84: They're here! The bandits are here!
86:
They're finally here... Well, that's that
then. It's been a good 80-odd years.
87: Tell grandma I love her. I'm going in!
91:
Hold on, hold on. Nobody said
anything about you having to fight.
Just hang back, throw some stones,
and... glare menacingly at them or
something.
95: Grieg will take care of the rest.
103:
Alk and Nimbus are taking care of
the east and west gates. This one is
on you, Grieg!
116:
We've gotta get going. We need to
hand over every single one of these
guys to the guild authorities!
118:
Ah, Grieg... You've become such a
wonderful young man.
122:
On behalf of everyone, I'd like to
offer our gratitude. Thank you so
much for staying by Grieg's side.
125: There's nothing to thank us for, really!
128:
As you can plainly see, this village is
mostly comprised of old men like
me. Grieg never had any other
friends to play with growing up...
129:
We were always worried about what
he would do in the future, given his...
reckless nature.
131:
But it seems that's a matter of the
past. He's found new, trustworthy
companions.
135:
Hey, everyone! What's the holdup?
You're gonna get left behind!
138:
Please, protect that boy. We ask only
this of you.
142:
Of course! Though, to be fair, we're
not the only ones doing the
protecting. We rely on him a bunch
too!
146:
What were you guys talking about?
Oh gosh, I hope the elder didn't tell
you about me when I was younger...
I was so stupid back then!
150:
Haha. It was something like that, I
suppose.
